7.7 Operator Integration Workflow
A clean integration between systems should look like this:


Discovery (DaDD™)
 → Capture metrics → Confirm repeatability → Log Process Yes.
Anchoring / Tic-Tac-Toe™
 → Gain A/B/C definition alignment → Log Definition Yes.
Power Transfer (QOA™)
 → Offer verification control → Log Control Yes.
C.A.D.E.N.C.E.™ Execution
 → Automate post-meeting verification → Record confirmations.
RMSP™ Reinforcement
 → Legal clauses finalize credit logic → All automation synced.
Offer Triangle Reinforcement
 → Frame engagement as risk-balanced governance for internal leadership.

Result:
Every moving piece - discovery, definition, verification, legal, and communication - functions as a closed-loop system. The engagement becomes self-governing, board-defensible, and renewal-ready.


7.8 Instructor Summary

Purpose: To synchronize QOA™ with the rest of the Advisory operating stack so that it functions as a controlled, compliant, and scalable risk-transfer mechanism.


Outcome: Every engagement can now be run through a repeatable pattern:

Data proven in Discovery.
Logic aligned in Tic-Tac-Toe™.
Verification automated in C.A.D.E.N.C.E.™.
Milestones enforced through RMSP™.
Executive comprehension secured via Offer Framing.
This integration converts QOA™ from a conversational close into an operational standard.
It becomes the final layer of a full-stack Advisory system - measurable, defensible, and elegant.


